				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The ultimate solution is to make an NES program that can be used with a ruler. It would display a box with a constant height (200px) and a variable width (144px to 200px). Then everybody with a devcart could measure their TVs once and for all to establish what ratios are found in the wild.</div>
<br />
<br />This should work: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/demos/square.zip">http://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/demos/square.zip</a><!-- m --></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					
