					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Will this new NTSC emulation have any benefit for PC's hooked up to CRT based NTSC televisions, or is it only useful for emulating on a PC's CRT?  This looks like NES emulation as taken another leap in accuracy.  Is anything like this necessary for audio?
<br />
<br />After this, what is the most lacking aspect of best of breed NES emulation?  Yes there will always be obscure pirate mappers that still need to be emulated, but what about stuff like controller input port latency?  How cycle accurate is that?  It seems like PC USB input devices would introduce latency that doesn't exist in a real NES, but what can an emulator do about it?</div>

